commit.message:
Add `--transport` option to port-forward

The latest Kubernetes beta supports using websockets for port-forward.
We now introduce a similar option to `attach` and `exec` to be able to
select the new transport.

See: https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/issues/4006

Signed-off-by: Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com>

verification.payload:
tree fc7014f4b244a7e054da4465c4fa51ad9f4b6faa

author Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com> 1711364309 +0100
committer Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com> 1711438235 +0100

Add `--transport` option to port-forward

The latest Kubernetes beta supports using websockets for port-forward.
We now introduce a similar option to `attach` and `exec` to be able to
select the new transport.

See: https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/issues/4006

Signed-off-by: Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com>

commit.message:
Do not auto find runtime handler for user namespaces tests

We rely on the test context runtime handler, which can be empty (`""`)
for the default one reported by the runtime.

Signed-off-by: Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com>
